panels.content:
# Workhorse 502s and 503s

The rate at which we're experiencing 502 and 503 errors is elevated.
This could be due to timeouts.

But what is causing the timeouts?

Lower is better.

# Web Apdex

What percentage of web requests complete within the cutoff threshold?

We can see that latency spikes lead to the 502/503 errors we see in Workhorse, in the top panel

Higher is better.

panels.description: Apdex is a measure of requests that complete within a tolerable period of time for the service. Higher is better.

targets.expr:
min by (type) (min_over_time(gitlab_service_apdex:ratio{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"}[$__interval]))
or
min by (type) (gitlab_service_apdex:ratio{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="web"})
avg by (type) (avg_over_time(gitlab_service_apdex:ratio{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"}[$__interval]))

min by (type) (gitlab_service_apdex:ratio{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"} offset 1w)
or
min by (type) (gitlab_service_apdex:ratio{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="web"} offset 1w)

panels.title: Latency: Apdex

panels.content:
# Web Errors

What percentage of web requests fail?

Lower is better.

panels.description: Error rates are a measure of unhandled service exceptions within a minute period. Client errors are excluded when possible. Lower is better

targets.expr:
clamp_max(
  max by (type) (max_over_time(gitlab_service_errors:ratio_5m{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"}[$__interval]))
  or
  sum by (type) (gitlab_service_errors:ratio_5m{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="web"}),
  1
)

clamp_max(
  avg by (type) (avg_over_time(gitlab_service_errors:ratio_5m{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"}[$__interval])),
  1
)

max by (type) (gitlab_service_errors:ratio_5m{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="web"} offset 1w)
or
sum by (type) (gitlab_service_errors:ratio_5m{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="web"} offset 1w)

panels.title: Error Ratios

panels.span:
Postgres sync connection pool saturation per database node.

Web/api/git applications use a separate connection pool to sidekiq.

When this resource is saturated, web/api database operations may queue, leading to unicorn/puma saturation and 503 errors in the web.
 Lower is better.

targets.expr:
clamp_min(
  clamp_max(
    max by(environment, tier, type, stage, fqdn, instance) (
  clamp_min(
    clamp_max(
      (
        pgbouncer_pools_server_active_connections{user="gitlab", database="gitlabhq_production", environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main"} +
        pgbouncer_pools_server_testing_connections{user="gitlab", database="gitlabhq_production", environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main"} +
        pgbouncer_pools_server_used_connections{user="gitlab", database="gitlabhq_production", environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main"} +
        pgbouncer_pools_server_login_connections{user="gitlab", database="gitlabhq_production", environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main"}
      )
      / on(environment, tier, type, stage, fqdn, instance) group_left()
      sum by (environment, tier, type, stage, fqdn, instance) (
        pgbouncer_databases_pool_size{name="gitlabhq_production", environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main"}
      )
      ,
      1)
  ,
  0)
)

  ,1)
,0)

clamp_min(
  clamp_max(
    max(
      max_over_time(
        gitlab_component_saturation:ratio{environment="$environment", type="pgbouncer", stage="main", component="pgbouncer_sync_pool"}[$__interval]
      )
    ) by (component)
  ,1)
,0)

panels.title: pgbouncer_sync_pool component saturation: Postgres Sync (Web/API) Connection Pool Saturation per Node

panels.content:
### Is this being caused by more database traffic?

# Patroni QPS

It doesn't appear to be. Patroni QPS seems to be stable over the long term.

panels.description: The operation rate is the sum total of all requests being handle for all components within this service. Note that a single user request can lead to requests to multiple components. Higher is busier.

targets.expr:
avg by (type)
(avg_over_time(gitlab_service_ops:rate_5m{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="patroni"}[$__interval]) or avg_over_time(gitlab_service_ops:rate{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="patroni"}[$__interval]))
or
sum by (type) (gitlab_service_ops:rate_5m{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="patroni"} or gitlab_service_ops:rate{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="patroni"})

avg by (type) (
  gitlab_service_ops:rate_5m{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="patroni"} offset 1w
  or
  gitlab_service_ops:rate{env="$environment", environment="$environment", monitor="global", stage="main", type="patroni"} offset 1w
)
or
sum by (type) (
  gitlab_service_ops:rate_5m{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="patroni"} offset 1w
  or
  gitlab_service_ops:rate{environment="$environment", monitor!~"global|", stage="main", type="patroni"} offset 1w
)
